ATM Con-artists Michael Manyana, 51, and Millicent Mkhwanazi, 48, were sentenced by the Khayelitsha Magistrate&#8217;s Court in December to 53 and 50 Years respectively for their role as the leaders of the syndicate.They took advantage of pensioners, students and tourists for more than seven years.Mkhwanazi broke down during the trial and pleaded for leniency, but Manyana refused to admit he appeared in CCTV footage that was central in convicting the pair.Manyana continued to deny it was him even though his face can celarly be seen in the footage.